Hello Adam=2C

As a valued investor in our initial Liquidity fund=2C we are delighted to=
 extend an invitation for you to participate in the newly-launched Liquidi=
ty 7 Fund.

Liquidity Group=2C an AI-based assessment management firm with headquarter=
s in Abu Dhabi and Tel Aviv=2C specializes in developing AI technologies f=
or financial applications and manages credit and equity investments with a=
 total AUM of $2.5 billion=2C consisting of $2 billion in venture debt fun=
ds and $0.5 billion in equity investments.

In collaboration with Harel Insurance Group=2C Liquidity Group recently an=
nounced the launch of a new $200m debt fund named =E2=80=9CLiquidity 7=E2=
=80=9D. This fund is managed by a subsidiary of Liquidity Group and is reg=
ulated by the Commission for the Supervision of the Financial Sector (CSSF=
) in Luxembourg.

With five additional debt funds=2C collectively managing over $2 billion=
=2C we are now=2C for the first time since 2019=2C exclusively offering ou=
r qualified Liquidity fund investors the opportunity to leverage their exp=
erience and join the new Liquidity 7 fund=2C alongside premier institution=
al investors.

You can read more about Harel=E2=80=99s decision to join Liquidity 7 in th=
is recently-published Calcalist article (https://www.calcalistech.com/ctec=
hnews/article/s1v00mfqup?utm_source=3DHEB_English&utm_campaign=3D46af97701=
d-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2024_01_22_03_48_COPY_09&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_term=3D0_=
-5751f656e8-%5BLIST_EMAIL_ID%5D) .

The newly established Fund=2C managed by Liquidity Group=2C is set to inve=
st in growth-stage technology companies across Asia Pacific=2C the USA=2C=
 and Europe. It will operate in conjunction with other debt funds and inve=
stment vehicles under Liquidity Group's management. The Fund's management=
 company holds a license that specifically allows it to provide commercial=
 loans to companies in Germany. This is significant as Germany represents=
 a highly regulated market with strong demand=2C where operating as a lend=
er requires specific licensing.

Investments will be conducted utilizing Liquidity=E2=80=99s advanced propr=
ietary risk prediction technology. This technology has been instrumental i=
n Liquidity Group's remarkable success in the credit sector=2C even amidst=
 global market uncertainties and major macro events like war and the COVID=
-19 pandemic.

The Fund is a key component of Liquidity Group's broader strategy that lev=
erages advanced AI and patented machine learning technologies for effectiv=
e capital allocation and management. In 2023=2C these technologies signifi=
cantly contributed to Liquidity Group's expansion. Notable milestones incl=
uded MUFG raising its investment commitment to $1 billion in the debt fund=
s=2C the creation of four new credit funds=2C and the launch of Liquidity=
=E2=80=99s inaugural equity investment fund. This equity fund=2C with a fo=
cus on technology companies and valued at $0.5 billion=2C was recently est=
ablished in Singapore in October 2023.

For more information and to register for access to the Fund=2C please foll=
ow this (https://liquiditygroup.com/funds/liquidity-7?utm_source=3DHEB_Eng=
lish&utm_campaign=3D46af97701d-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2024_01_22_03_48_COPY_09&utm=
_medium=3Demail&utm_term=3D0_-5751f656e8-%5BLIST_EMAIL_ID%5D) link (https:=
//liquiditygroup.com/funds/liquidity-7?utm_source=3DHEB_English&utm_campai=
gn=3D46af97701d-EMAIL_CAMPAIGN_2024_01_22_03_48_COPY_09&utm_medium=3Demail=
&utm_term=3D0_-5751f656e8-%5BLIST_EMAIL_ID%5D) .
*Subscription is conditional on filling out a Qualified Investor Declarati=
